snippet.title: 48 HOURS IN EDINBURGH - ft Speakeasy Bars, Freaky Orange Drink and Best Brunches
snippet.description:
Honestly, we had no idea we were going to love Edinburgh this much. Edinburgh isn't massive, but it's scene is. Edinburgh, Scotland's capital, is a beautiful city which isn't over populated so very easy to get around and enjoy. 48 Hours wasn't enough but we will back!

★ Sign up here for £10 off our Lightroom presets. 10 BIG beautiful presets to get the TOPJAW look: https://tinyurl.com/topjawfix ★

In order of appearance, the places we visited were:
Pizza Geeks - 19 Dalry Rd, EH11 2BQ - Pizza £6-11 Dragon Ballz £7
Pantry - 1 N W Circus Pl, EH3 6ST  - Pimp My Fry £11.75 - Stockbridge £10
Cold Town House - 4 Grassmarket, EH1 2JU - Flight of 4 x ⅓ Pint £7
IRN BRU - You can literally buy it anywhere in Edinburgh
Victoria Street - EH1 2HG
OINK - Various Locations but we went to 34 Victoria Street EH1 2JW - Hog Roas Roll £5.40
Wings - 5 - 7 Old Fishmarket Cl, EH1 1RW - Each plate £3.50
The Bon Vivant - 55 Thistle St, EH2 1DY - Platter £16, Cheese £14, Truffle Chips £4.50
Lucky Liquor - 39A Queen St, EH2 3NH - Cocktails £7-9.50
Panda & Sons - 79 Queen St, EH2 4NF - All cocktails £9
Cairngorm Coffee - 41A Frederick St, EH2 1EP - Toasted Banana Loaf £4.50, Reusen Sandwich £5, Flat White £2.80
Cafe St Honore - 34 Thistle St N W Ln, EH2 1EA - Venison £24, Creme Brulee £9
The Queens Arms - 49 Frederick St, EH2 1EP - Beer around £4/pint
Makars Gourmet Mash Bar - 9 N Bank St, EH1 2LP - Scotch Egg & Rosti £11, Lamb Shank £17
Aurora - 187 Great Jct St, EH6 5LQ - All dishes 12.95 each / two for 24.95
Nauticus - 142 Duke St, EH6 8HR - All cocktails £7.50/8
Alby’s - 8 Portland Place, EH6 4AR - Sandwiches £7/8
The Devil’s Advocate - 9 Advocate's Cl, EH1 1ND - God knows what Whiskey I had
Paradise Palms - 41 Lothian St, EH1 1HB - All cocktails £7-9
